						<summary>

						<p>Nandi-pillar set up in the temple of Gaṇēśa.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1438, Āshāḍha ba. 5,</hi> corresponding to 1516 A.D., June 24 Tuesday. In this record the cyclic year is damaged. The Śaka year 1438 falls in Dhātri.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to refer to a gift for the merit of Siddha Bhikshā vṛitti-Ayyaṅgāru by his agent.</p>						

						</summary>
